Very good, very easy. Made a couple small changes: I baked tortilla triangles (corn and flour) at 350 with some oliver oil and kosher salt for about 15 minutes. (I like the flour tortillas better; easier to eat in a salad.) I grilled the corn, as many other reviewers did, adding olive oil, salt & sugar to the cobs prior to grilling. Next time, I think I'll add some avocado slices to garnish along with the tortillas.

